âœ… Step 3 â€” Apply your tab-style look to Kendo Menu

Now open legacy-modern.css and add the following block at the bottom.

This transforms Kendoâ€™s menu into your â€œtabâ€ look.

ğŸ¨ ğŸ“¦ Modern Legacy Tab Styling for Kendo Menu
/* -------------------------------------------------------
   KENDO MENU AS LEGACY TABS
------------------------------------------------------- */

.legacy-kendo-menu {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #000;
    padding: 0;
}

/* Top-level menu items */
.legacy-kendo-menu .k-item > .k-link {
    background-color: silver;
    border: 1px solid #000;
    border-bottom: 0;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    margin-right: 4px;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
}

/* On hover */
.legacy-kendo-menu .k-item > .k-link:hover {
    background-color: #fff;
}

/* Selected item */
.legacy-kendo-menu .k-state-selected > .k-link,
.legacy-kendo-menu .k-item.k-state-active > .k-link {
    background-color: #fff;
    font-weight: bold;
    border-bottom: 0;
}

/* Submenu styling */
.legacy-kendo-menu .k-group {
    border: 1px solid #888;
    background-color: #f7f7f7;
}

.legacy-kendo-menu .k-group .k-item > .k-link {
    padding: 5px 10px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
}

/* Hover for submenu items */
.legacy-kendo-menu .k-group .k-item > .k-link:hover {
    background-color: #e3eaeb;
}

